  "abstract": "Particulate organic matter carbon (POM-C) and mineral-associated organic carbon (MAOC) represent contrasting soil carbon fractions POM-C as a labile, short-term nutrient source and MAOC as a stable, long-term carbon reservoir critical for evaluating soil health and management impacts. Understanding the balance between these fractions provides critical insights into soil carbon storage, stability, and response to management practices.",
